725391f-d.title: Queens: 50th Street - 25th Avenue
725391f-d.text:
50th Street, (in line thereof) north of Twenty-fifth Averue (probably in St. Michaels Cemetery), showinor four views of hhe D. Riler farmhouse. It was erected by Abraham Riker about 1717. Additions have since it was first erected been made. The British plundered tuis house when it was occupied by dacobus Riker in 1776. See other views for more
data.
April 1923
Views 1,2 3 and 4
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
